Title: INTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: ROOF HEADLINING: DISASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

DISASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE NO. 1 ROOF SILENCER PAD (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the No. 1 roof silencer pad.

2. REMOVE NO. 2 ROOF SILENCER PAD (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the No. 2 roof silencer pad.

3. REMOVE NO. 2 ANTENNA CORD SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

4. REMOVE VANITY LIGHT ASSEMBLY

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

(a) Disengage the 2 claws (A) and separate the bulb holder from the vanity light assembly as shown in the illustration.

*1

Bulb Holder

*a

Claw (A)

*b

Claw (B)

(b) Disengage the claw (B) to remove the vanity light assembly.

5. REMOVE NO. 1 ROOF WIRE

(a) Remove the adhesive tape from the roof headlining assembly.

w/o Sliding Roof

*B

w/ Sliding Roof

*C

*D

*E

(b) Turn the 2 visor connectors counterclockwise approximately 90° and remove them from the roof headlining assembly.

*B

(c) Disengage each clamp and remove the No. 1 roof wire from the roof headlining assembly.

6. REMOVE FRONT SIDE RAIL SPACER LH (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the front side rail spacer LH.

7. REMOVE FRONT SIDE RAIL SPACER RH (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the front side rail spacer RH.

8. REMOVE NO. 2 ROOF HEADLINING SET PLATE LH (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the No. 2 roof headlining set plate LH.

9. REMOVE NO. 2 ROOF HEADLINING SET PLATE RH (w/o Sliding Roof)

(a) Remove the No. 2 roof headlining set plate RH.

10. REMOVE NO. 2 ROOF HEADLINING PAD

(a) Remove the No. 2 roof headlining pad.

11. REMOVE ROOF HEADLINING PAD

(a) Remove the roof headlining pad.
